## Phase I: Database Design & ETL (Milestone: 10 March)

### Database Schema (MySQL 8.0, InnoDB)

```
LOOKUP TABLES
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
primary_for              best_subject_area
────────────             ─────────────────
for_code     PK (INT)    area_id   PK (INT AUTO_INCREMENT)
description  VARCHAR     area_name VARCHAR
                         (NOTE: for_code is mostly INT but some
                          entries are text — store as VARCHAR, be careful)

conferences                          journals
───────────                          ────────
conf_id      PK (INT AUTO_INCREMENT) journal_id   PK (INT AUTO_INCREMENT)
title        VARCHAR                 title        VARCHAR
acronym      VARCHAR                 country      VARCHAR
rank         ENUM('A*','A','B','C')  publisher    VARCHAR
primary_for  INT  FK→primary_for     sjr_index    DECIMAL
dblp_key     VARCHAR (nullable)      cite_score   DECIMAL
                                     h_index      INT
                                     best_quartile ENUM('Q1','Q2','Q3','Q4')
                                     best_subject_area INT FK→best_subject_area
                                     total_docs   INT
                                     total_refs   INT
                                     total_cites_3y INT
                                     citable_docs_3y INT
                                     cites_per_doc_2y DECIMAL
                                     refs_per_doc DECIMAL

authors
───────
author_id    PK (INT AUTO_INCREMENT)
name         VARCHAR

FACTUAL TABLES
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
papers                               paper_authors
──────                               ─────────────
paper_id     PK (INT AUTO_INCREMENT) paper_id     FK→papers   ┐ composite PK
title        VARCHAR                 author_id    FK→authors  ┘
year         INT                     author_order INT  ← position in author list
pages        VARCHAR
type         ENUM('conference','journal')
conf_id      INT FK→conferences  (NULL if journal)
journal_id   INT FK→journals     (NULL if conference)
volume       VARCHAR (nullable, journals only)
number       VARCHAR (nullable)
dblp_key     VARCHAR
ee           VARCHAR
url          VARCHAR

CHECK CONSTRAINT: (conf_id IS NOT NULL) XOR (journal_id IS NOT NULL)
```

### Design Trade-offs: Single `papers` Table vs Two Tables

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Decision: Single `papers` table** with a `type` column and nullable FKs.
>
> | | Single table | Two tables (`conf_papers` + `journal_articles`) |
> |---|---|---|
> | Cross-type queries (e.g. all papers by an author) | ✅ Simple JOIN | ❌ UNION needed |
> | Author profile (conf + journal per year) | ✅ One query | ❌ Two queries + UNION |
> | Year profile (total papers) | ✅ One query | ❌ UNION |
> | Data integrity | ⚠️ Nullable FKs (mitigated by CHECK) | ✅ Cleaner NULLs |
> | Schema clarity | ⚠️ Mixed fields | ✅ Clear separation |
>
> The professor explicitly asks about cross-type queries (author profiles combining conf + journal publications), so the single-table approach wins here.

### ETL Pipeline

```
etl/
├── 01_create_schema.sql      DDL — create all tables, PKs, FKs, indexes
├── 02_clean_inproceedings.py Extract + clean conference papers CSV
├── 03_clean_articles.py      Extract + clean journal articles CSV  
├── 04_load_lookups.py        Load: primary_for, best_subject_area,
│                             conferences (iCORE26), journals (Kaggle)
│                             authors (extracted from both DBLP files)
├── 05_match_conferences.py   Match DBLP booktitle → iCORE26 acronym
│                             (exact match first, then fuzzy/regex)
├── 06_match_journals.py      Match DBLP journal name → Kaggle title
│                             (regex normalization: remove punctuation,
│                              lowercase, handle "IEEE Trans. on X" patterns)
├── 07_load_papers.py         Load papers + paper_authors with FK resolution
├── 08_create_views.sql       SQL views for all common queries
└── 09_backup.bat             mysqldump backup (Windows .bat)
```

**Matching strategy** (steps 05 & 06):
1. Exact string match (after lowercasing + stripping spaces)
2. Acronym match for conferences (DBLP `booktitle` = iCORE26 `Acronym`)
3. Regex normalization (remove "The", "Journal of", punctuation, etc.)
4. Unmatched entries → loaded with `NULL` FK (still valid, just unranked)

