## Phase II: Application Prototype (Milestone: 21 April)

### Technology Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Database | MySQL 8.0 (InnoDB) |
| Backend | Python 3 + Flask |
| DB Access | `mysql-connector-python` — all processing done in MySQL via views/queries |
| Frontend | HTML/CSS/JS |
| Charts | **D3.js** — premium animated line, bar, scatter plots |
| Styling | Custom CSS (dark theme, modern design) |

### Project Structure

```
project/
├── data/                         Raw CSV data
├── etl/                          Phase I scripts (see above)
├── backend/
│   ├── app.py                    Flask app entry point
│   ├── db.py                     MySQL connection helper
│   ├── config.py                 DB credentials, settings
│   └── routes/
│       ├── conferences.py        /api/conference/<id>/profile, /stats, /papers
│       ├── journals.py           /api/journal/<id>/profile, /stats, /papers
│       ├── authors.py            /api/author/<id>/profile, /papers-by-year
│       ├── years.py              /api/year/<y>/profile, /papers
│       └── charts.py             /api/charts/linechart, /barchart, /scatter
├── frontend/
│   ├── templates/                Jinja2 HTML templates (served by Flask)
│   │   ├── base.html
│   │   ├── index.html
│   │   ├── conference.html
│   │   ├── journal.html
│   │   ├── author.html
│   │   ├── year.html
│   │   └── charts.html
│   └── static/
│       ├── css/style.css
│       ├── js/d3-charts.js       All D3.js chart components
│       └── js/app.js             UI logic, API calls, filters
├── deliverables/
├── README.md
└── requirements.txt
```

> [!NOTE]
> Flask's `template_folder` will be set to `'../frontend/templates'` and `static_folder` to `'../frontend/static'` in `app.py` to support the `frontend/` layout.

