## Phase III: Full Interactive Application (Hard Deadline: 26 May)

### Required Features

#### Conference / Journal Profile
- Ranking info (rank, PrimaryFoR / BestSubjectArea, SJR, H-index…)
- Line charts: papers/year, total authors/year, distinct authors/year
- Stats: first/last year, total papers, avg papers/year, avg authors/paper, avg authors/year
- **Year range filter** on all of the above
- Scrollable table of all papers (filterable by year range)

#### Year Profile
- Total papers, distinct journals, distinct conferences, total & distinct authors
- Paper details table with filter by conference / journal / author

#### Author Profile
- First/last known year, total papers, avg papers/year
- Line chart: papers/year broken down by conference vs journal

#### Targeted Charts Page
| Chart Type | Options |
|-----------|---------|
| **Line** | Papers (or authors) per year for selected conferences/journals |
| **Line** | # conferences/journals per category (PrimaryFoR or BestSubjectArea) per year |
| **Bar** | Total papers / avg papers/year / avg authors/year per conference/journal |
| **Bar** | Per publisher: # journals total + # journals per quartile (4 series Q1–Q4) |
| **Scatter** | Any 2 of: TotalDocs, TotalRefs, TotalCites3y, CitableDocs3y, Cites/Doc2y, Refs/Doc |
| **Scatter** | Avg authors vs # papers per year (for conferences or journals) |

#### Interactivity
- Search/dropdown for conference, journal, author selection
- Year range filters (from / to)
- Multi-select for comparison line/bar charts
- All queries parameterized and executed inside MySQL (no full-table pull to app memory)

---

## Verification Plan

1. **ETL checks**: row counts, FK integrity, no orphan records, author N:M correctness
2. **Sample queries**: manually verify stats (e.g. EDBT papers in 2020) against raw CSV
3. **API tests**: check all endpoints return correct JSON
4. **UI**: manually navigate every page, verify all charts render with real data
5. **Filters**: test year range, author/conf/journal selection on all pages

---

## Decisions Made

- ✅ MySQL 8.0 (already installed)
- ✅ Team: AM 4855 & AM 5381
- ✅ Tech stack: Python + Flask + D3.js
- ✅ Single `papers` table (documented trade-offs above)
- ✅ `author_order` in `paper_authors`
- ✅ `primary_for` and `best_subject_area` as proper FK lookup tables
- ✅ Conference matching DBLP↔iCORE26 (acronym + fuzzy)
- ✅ Backup as `.bat` (Windows compatible)
- ✅ Flask served from `backend/`, templates via custom `template_folder` path
